-- Czech Stocks: Erste Group, New World Resources, Vienna Insurance
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-04-27T15:09:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-27/czech-stocks-erste-group-new-world-resources-vienna-insurance.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
rose 0.5 percent to 935 at the close in Prague. The gauge gained
0.9 percent this week, paring April losses to 3.9 percent.  The following were among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Vienna Insurance Group AG (VIG)   climbed 2.5 percent to
766.5 koruna and  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)   of  Austria  added
0.6 percent to 426 koruna. Financial stocks were among the best
performers in  Europe  as results from Vinci SA to Sandvik AB
topped estimates, overshadowing slower U.S. economic growth than
forecast.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the biggest Czech coking-
coal producer, rose 1.2 percent to 127.63 koruna, paring its
April losses to 3.7 percent. Deutsche Bank AG raised the stock
to hold from sell today, citing an improved outlook for the
commodity’s price and sales.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  